      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "2. Sean $y$, $x_1$, $x_2$ y $D=\\{0,1\\}$ variables aleatorias y una forma funcional de la esperanza condicional de la forma:\n",
        "$$\\mathbb{E}[ y|x_{1} ,x_{2} ,D] =e^{\\beta _{1} +\\beta _{2} x_{1} +\\beta _{3} x_{2} +\\gamma D}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "  Al respecto, determine el Efecto Marginal de $x_2$ y $D$."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6J9nrQ0eods7"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### Solución Ejercicio 1.1.2:"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FtEvF9anzQno"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Si $y=e^{\\beta _{1} +\\beta _{2} x_{1} +\\beta _{3} x_{2} +\\gamma D}$, entonces: $\\ln( y) =\\beta _{1} +\\beta _{2} x_{1} +\\beta _{3} x_{2} +\\gamma D$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yGsRB5z7p-If"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Por lo tanto tenemos que:"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mPwGExq7qp_7"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "$EMg_{x_{2}} =\\frac{\\partial \\ln( y)}{\\partial x_{2}} =\\beta _{3} y$\n",
        "\n",
        "y\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\begin{array}{{>{\\displaystyle}l}}\n",
        "EMg_{D} =\\mathbb{E}[ y|D=1,x_{1} ,x_{2} ,\\gamma ] -\\mathbb{E}[ y|D=0,x_{1} ,x_{2} ,\\gamma ] =\\left[ e^{\\beta _{1} +\\beta _{2} x_{1} +\\beta _{3} x_{2} +\\gamma ( 1)}\\right] -\\left[ e^{\\beta _{1} +\\beta _{2} x_{1} +\\beta _{3} x_{2} +\\gamma ( 0)}\\right]\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=e^{\\beta _{1} +\\beta _{2} x_{1} +\\beta _{3} x_{2} +\\gamma } -e^{\\beta _{1} +\\beta _{2} x_{1} +\\beta _{3} x_{2}} =\\left( e^{\\gamma } -1\\right) e^{\\beta _{1} +\\beta _{2} x_{1} +\\beta _{3} x_{2}}\n",
        "\\end{array}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XsngmlinzA36"
      }
