      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "En esta sección plantearemos un caso típico del método de Variables Instrumentales. Para lo cual le pedimos seguir la discusión y realizar las actividades que se le piden. Consideremos un modelo de equilibrio de mercado\n",
        "(la discusión original se encuentra en el trabajo de *Working (1927). What do statistical demand curves show?. Quaterly Journal of Economics, 41 pp. 212 - 235)*. Supongamos que tenemos el siguiente modelo de demanda o modelo\n",
        "en su forma estructural:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\begin{array}{ c c c }\n",
        "q^{d} & = & \\alpha _{0} +\\alpha _{1} p_{i} +u_{i}\\\\\n",
        "q^{s} & = & \\beta _{0} +\\beta _{1} p_{i} +v_{i}\n",
        "\\end{array}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "\\\n",
        "\n",
        "Donde $q^d$ es la cantidad demandada para el bien en cuestión, $q^s$ es la\n",
        "cantidad ofertada, $p_i$ es el precio de dicho bien. Los términos de error $u_i$ y $v_i$ representan otros factores observables que afectan o desplazan a la cantidad ofertada y a la cantidad demandada. Podemos asumir que dichos elementos $u_i$ y $v_i$ son factores no observables. De esta forma $\\mathbb{E}[u_i] = 0$ y que $\\mathbb{E}[v_i] = 0$. Adicionalment, suponga que que $Cov[u_i, v_i] = 0$ y que $q^d = q^s = q$, de tal forma que el mercado está en equilibrio, por lo que tenemos:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{gather}\n",
        "\\begin{array}{ c c c }\n",
        "q & = & \\alpha _{0} +\\alpha _{1} p_{i} +u_{i}\n",
        "\\end{array} \\tag{1.3}\\\\\n",
        "\\begin{array}{ c c c }\n",
        "q & = & \\beta _{0} +\\beta _{1} p_{i} +v_{i}\n",
        "\\end{array} \\tag{1.4}\n",
        "\\end{gather}\n",
        "\n",
        "\\\n",
        "\n",
        "Ambas ecuaciones tienen problemas de endogeneidad, ya que el precio $p_i$ es endógeno en cada una de las ecuaciones, ya que se determina simúltaneamente.\n",
        "\n",
        "Utilizando las ecuaciones ([1.3](#mjx-eqn-eq1.3)) y ([1.4](#mjx-eqn-eq1.4)) obtenga la ecuación de demanda y oferta:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "q_{i} =\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{\\alpha _{1} v_{i} -\\beta _{1} u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} \\tag{1.5}\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "p_{i} =\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} \\tag{1.6}\n",
        "\\end{equation}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YOhXXoAkP-a1"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Solución Ejercicio 1.2.1:"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "okVmlHnrY1gi"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "I) Despejando $p_i$ de ([1.3](#mjx-eqn-eq1.3)) y ([1.4](#mjx-eqn-eq1.4)):\n",
        "\n",
        "$q=\\alpha _{0} +\\alpha _{1} p_{i} +u_{i} \\longrightarrow \\alpha _{1} p_{i} =q-\\alpha _{0} -u_{i} \\longrightarrow p_{i} =\\frac{q-\\alpha _{0} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "y\n",
        "\n",
        "$q=\\beta _{0} +\\beta _{1} p_{i} +v_{i} \\longrightarrow \\beta _{1} p_{i} =q-\\beta _{0} -v_{i} \\longrightarrow p_{i} =\\frac{q-\\beta _{0} -v_{i}}{\\beta _{1}}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "D_WRDICGYz9I"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "II) Planteando $p_i = p_i$, es decir, igualar las dos ecuaciones obtenidas:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\begin{array}{{>{\\displaystyle}l}}\n",
        "p_{i} =p_{i} \\longrightarrow \\frac{q-\\alpha _{0} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1}} =\\frac{q-\\beta _{0} -v_{i}}{\\beta _{1}} \\longrightarrow \\beta _{1}( q-\\alpha _{0} -u_{i}) =\\alpha _{1}( q-\\beta _{0} -v_{i})\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\beta _{1} q-\\beta _{1} \\alpha _{0} -\\beta _{1} u_{i} =\\alpha _{1} q-\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{1} v_{i} \\longrightarrow \\beta _{1} q-\\alpha _{1} q=-\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{1} v_{i} +\\beta _{1} \\alpha _{0} +\\beta _{1} u_{i}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "q( \\beta _{1} -\\alpha _{1}) =-\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{1} v_{i} +\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1} +\\beta _{1} u_{i} \\longrightarrow q=\\frac{-\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{1} v_{i} +\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1} +\\beta _{1} u_{i}}{\\beta _{1} -\\alpha _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "q=\\frac{-( \\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} +\\alpha _{1} v_{i} -\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1} -\\beta _{1} u_{i})}{-( \\alpha _{1} +\\beta _{1})} \\longrightarrow q=\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1} +\\alpha _{1} v_{i} -\\beta _{1} u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} +\\beta _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\therefore q_i=\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1}}{\\alpha _{1} +\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{\\alpha _{1} v_{i} -\\beta _{1} u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} +\\beta _{1}}\n",
        "\\end{array}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4OuhioJB9FXu"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "III) Planteando $q = q$, es decir, igualando ([1.3](#mjx-eqn-eq1.3)) y ([1.4](#mjx-eqn-eq1.4)):\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\begin{array}{{>{\\displaystyle}l}}\n",
        "q=q\\longrightarrow \\alpha _{0} +\\alpha _{1} p_{i} +u_{i} =\\beta _{0} +\\beta _{1} p_{i} +v_{i} \\longrightarrow \\alpha _{1} p_{i} -\\beta _{1} p_{i} =\\beta _{0} +v_{i} -\\alpha _{0} -u_{i}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "p_{i}( \\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}) =\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} +v_{i} -u_{i} \\longrightarrow p_{i} =\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} +v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\therefore p_{i} =\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\n",
        "\\end{array}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5-D2qzEs_Wf-"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "De esta forma hemos obtenido dos expresiones ([1.5](#mjx-eqn-eq1.5)), ecuación de demanda, y ([1.6](#mjx-eqn-eq1.6)), ecuación de oferta, que representan la solución para el sistema de ecuaciones. No obstante, se puede apreciar que cada una de las variables tiene infuencia del término de error de cada una de las ecuaciones, por lo que NO se pueden separar enteramente y se suele decir que tenemos un problema de endogeneidad.\n",
        "\n",
        "A partir de la ecuación ([1.6](#mjx-eqn-eq1.6)), determine la covarianza entre $p_i$ y cada uno de los factores de cambio de la demanda $(u_i)$ y de la oferta $(v_i)$. Muestre que es igual a:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "Cov( p_{i} ,u_{i}) =-\\frac{Var( u_{i})}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} \\tag{1.7}\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "Cov( p_{i} ,v_{i}) =\\frac{Var( v_{i})}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} \\tag{1.8}\n",
        "\\end{equation}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KL-k-Z3MY7_U"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Solución Ejercicio 1.2.2:"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n82KHQRraVag"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "I) Recordemos que:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\mathbb{E}[u_i] = 0$ y $\\mathbb{E}[v_i] = 0$\n",
        "\n",
        "$Var( X) =\\mathbb{E}\\left[ X^{2}\\right] -\\mathbb{E}[ X]^{2}$\n",
        "\n",
        "$Cov( X,Y) =\\mathbb{E}[ XY] -\\mathbb{E}[ X]\\mathbb{E}[ Y]$\n",
        "\n",
        "Además: $\\mathbb{E}[ u_{i} v_{i}] =\\mathbb{E}[ v_{i}]\\mathbb{E}[ u_{i}] \\longrightarrow$ Ya que $u_i$ y $v_i$ son independientes"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "iA3Nnflka0BT"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "II) Despejando $p_i$ de ([1.9](#mjx-eqn-eq1.9)):\n",
        "\n",
        "$q_{i} =\\beta _{0} +\\beta _{1} p_{i} +\\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\zeta _{i} \\longrightarrow \\beta _{1} p_{i} =q_{i} -\\beta _{0} -\\beta _{2} x_{i} -\\zeta _{i} \\longrightarrow p_{i} =\\frac{q_{i} -\\beta _{0} -\\beta _{2} x_{i} -\\zeta _{i}}{\\beta _{1}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "Y anteriormente despejamos $p_i$ de ([1.3](#mjx-eqn-eq1.3)):\n",
        "\n",
        "$p_{i} =\\frac{q_i-\\alpha _{0} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1}}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GYET4Szca4j-"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "II) Entonces:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\begin{array}{{>{\\displaystyle}l}}\n",
        "Cov( p_{i} ,u_{i}) =\\mathbb{E}[ p_{i} \\cdotp u_{i}] -\\mathbb{E}[ p_{i}] \\cdotp \\mathbb{E}[ u_{i}] =\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\left(\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right) \\cdot u_{i}\\right] -\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right] \\cdotp \\mathbb{E}[ u_{i}]\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\left(\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} +v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right) \\cdot u_{i}\\right] -\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} +v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right] \\cdotp 0=\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\frac{\\beta _{0} u_{i} -\\alpha _{0} u_{i} +v_{i} u_{i} -u_{i} u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right] -0\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\frac{\\beta _{0} u_{i} -\\alpha _{0} u_{i} +v_{i} u_{i} -u_{i}^{2}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right] =\\frac{\\mathbb{E}\\left[ \\beta _{0} u_{i} -\\alpha _{0} u_{i} +v_{i} u_{i} -u_{i}^{2}\\right]}{\\mathbb{E}[ \\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}]} =\\frac{\\mathbb{E}[ \\beta _{0} u_{i}] -\\mathbb{E}[ \\alpha _{0} u_{i}] +\\mathbb{E}[ v_{i} u_{i}] -\\mathbb{E}\\left[ u_{i}^{2}\\right]}{\\mathbb{E}[ \\alpha _{1}] -\\mathbb{E}[ \\beta _{1}]}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=\\frac{\\mathbb{\\beta _{0} \\cdot E}[ u_{i}] -\\mathbb{\\alpha _{0} \\cdot E}[ u_{i}] +\\mathbb{E}[ u_{i}] \\cdot \\mathbb{E}[ v_{i}] -\\mathbb{E}\\left[ u_{i}^{2}\\right]}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} =\\frac{\\beta _{0} \\cdot 0-\\alpha _{0} \\cdot 0+0\\cdot 0-\\mathbb{E}\\left[ u_{i}^{2}\\right]}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=\\frac{0-0+0-\\mathbb{E}\\left[ u_{i}^{2}\\right]}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} =\\frac{-\\mathbb{E}\\left[ u_{i}^{2}\\right] +0}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} =\\frac{-\\mathbb{E}\\left[ u_{i}^{2}\\right] +\\mathbb{E}[ u_{i}]^{2}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} =\\frac{-\\left(\\mathbb{E}\\left[ u_{i}^{2}\\right] -\\mathbb{E}[ u_{i}]^{2}\\right)}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} =\\frac{-Var( u_{i})}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\therefore Cov( p_{i} ,u_{i}) =-\\frac{Var( u_{i})}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\n",
        "\\end{array}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cOyF5bd6CpUR"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "III) De forma similar:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\begin{array}{{>{\\displaystyle}l}}\n",
        "Cov( p_{i} ,v_{i}) =\\mathbb{E}[ p_{i} \\cdotp v_{i}] -\\mathbb{E}[ p_{i}] \\cdotp \\mathbb{E}[ v_{i}] =\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\left(\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right) \\cdot v_{i}\\right] -\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right] \\cdotp \\mathbb{E}[ v_{i}]\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\left(\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} +v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right) \\cdot v_{i}\\right] -\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} +v_{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right] \\cdotp 0=\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\frac{\\beta _{0} v_{i} -\\alpha _{0} v_{i} +v_{i} v_{i} -u_{i} v_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right] -0\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\frac{\\beta _{0} v_{i} -\\alpha _{0} v_{i} +v_{i} v_{i} -u_{i} v_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\right] =\\frac{\\mathbb{E}[ \\beta _{0} v_{i} -\\alpha _{0} v_{i} +v_{i} v_{i} -u_{i} v_{i}]}{\\mathbb{E}[ \\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}]} =\\frac{\\mathbb{E}[ \\beta _{0} v_{i}] -\\mathbb{E}[ \\alpha _{0} v_{i}] +\\mathbb{E}[ v_{i} v_{i}] -\\mathbb{E}[ u_{i} v_{i}]}{\\mathbb{E}[ \\alpha _{1}] -\\mathbb{E}[ \\beta _{1}]}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=\\frac{\\mathbb{\\beta _{0} \\cdot E}[ v_{i}] -\\mathbb{\\alpha _{0} \\cdot E}[ v_{i}] +\\mathbb{E}\\left[ v_{i}^{2}\\right] -\\mathbb{E}[ u_{i}] \\cdot \\mathbb{E}[ v_{i}]}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} =\\frac{\\mathbb{\\beta _{0} \\cdot } 0-\\mathbb{\\alpha _{0} \\cdot } 0+\\mathbb{E}\\left[ v_{i}^{2}\\right] -0\\cdot 0}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "=\\frac{0-0+\\mathbb{E}\\left[ v_{i}^{2}\\right] -0}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} =\\frac{\\mathbb{E}\\left[ v_{i}^{2}\\right] -0}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} =\\frac{\\mathbb{E}\\left[ v_{i}^{2}\\right] -\\mathbb{E}[ v_{i}]^{2}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\therefore Cov( p_{i} ,v_{i}) =\\frac{Var( v_{i})}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\n",
        "\\end{array}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0DoUB98FIvKd"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "De esta forma, el precio está correlacionado positivamente con los factores que modifican la demanda y negativamente con los facores que modifican la oferta, ello en razón de que la pendiente de la demanda es negativa $(\\alpha_1 < 0)$\n",
        "y la de la oferta es positiva $(\\beta_1 > 0)$. En este caso, decimos que el problema de endogenidad se origina por el proceso de equilibrio en el mercado\n",
        "\n",
        "La razón de la endogeniedad referida es que de la curva de demanda o de la  curva de oferta no es posible inferir si los cambios en el nivel de precios o en las cantidades en el mercado son por causa de desplazamientos de la curva de oferta o de la curva de demanda. Esto significa que sólo es posible estimar la curva de oferta o de demanda si es posible observar alguno de los factores que determinan a la demanda o la oferta.\n",
        "\n",
        "Supongamos que el efecto del termino de error en la cantidad ofertada, $v_i$, puede ser dividido en: los fatores observables que están asociados a la demanda $x_i$ y un factor no observable $\\zeta_i$ que no está correlacionado con $x_i$. Es decir, que tenemos una formulación de la ecuación de oferta similar a:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "q_{i} =\\beta _{0} +\\beta _{1} p_{i} +\\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\zeta_i \\tag{1.9}\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "\n",
        "De esta forma podemos decir que existe una posibilidad de que se elimine la endogeidad, esto es, que se pueda instrumentar mediante el uso de variables asociadas a la demanda $(x_i)$. Lo anterior, para efecto de separar del término de error la información que puede ser endogena al sistema, tal y como se muestra en la ecuación ([1.9](#mjx-eqn-eq1.9)). La Figura 1.1 ilustra esta discusión para cada uno de los casos: de la demanda y de la oferta.\n",
        "\n",
        "Esta discusión es una aplicación del Método de Variables Instrumentales (IV). Para el cual requerimos un regresor que es endógeno y que requerimos sea instrumentado. Al instrumento se le denomina variable instrumental. En este caso, es la variable $x_i$ quien sera nuestra variable instrumental. Retomemos nuestro sistema de ecuaciones de demanda y oferta. Si realizamos el mismo procedimiento de solución del sistema de ecuaciones pero considerando a la ecuación ([1.9](#mjx-eqn-eq1.9)).\n",
        "\n",
        "Dicho lo anterior, muestre que obtendríamos un sistema que quedaría como sigue:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "p_{i} =\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{\\beta _{2}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} x_{i} +\\frac{\\zeta _{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{i} -\\beta _{1}} \\tag {1.10}\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "q_{i} =\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{2}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\zeta _{i} -\\beta _{1} u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} \\tag {1.11}\n",
        "\\end{equation}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7xfOnHq5a1MH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Solución Ejercicio 1.2.3:"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NPbyhaNxOZDm"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "I) Planteando $q_i = q_i$, es decir, igualando las ecuaciones ([1.3](#mjx-eqn-eq1.3)) y ([1.9](#mjx-eqn-eq1.9)):\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\begin{array}{{>{\\displaystyle}l}}\n",
        "q_{i} =q_{i} \\longrightarrow \\alpha _{0} +\\alpha _{1} p_{i} +u_{i} =\\beta _{0} +\\beta _{1} p_{i} +\\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\zeta _{i} \\longrightarrow \\alpha _{1} p_{i} -\\beta _{1} p_{i} =\\beta _{0} +\\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\zeta _{i} -\\alpha _{0} -u_{i}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "p_{i}( \\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}) =\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} +\\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\zeta _{i} -u_{i} \\longrightarrow p_{i} =\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} +\\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\zeta _{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\therefore p_{i} =\\frac{\\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{\\beta _{2}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} x_{i} +\\frac{\\zeta _{i} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\n",
        "\\end{array}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HCoBlBAGOiSw"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "III) Planteando $p_i = p_i$, es decir, igualando los despejes anteriores:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\begin{array}{{>{\\displaystyle}l}}\n",
        "\\frac{q_{i} -\\alpha _{0} -u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1}} =\\frac{q_{i} -\\beta _{0} -\\beta _{2} x_{i} -\\zeta _{i}}{\\beta _{1}} \\longrightarrow \\beta _{1}( q_{i} -\\alpha _{0} -u_{i}) =\\alpha _{1}( q_{i} -\\beta _{0} -\\beta _{2} x_{i} -\\zeta _{i})\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\beta _{1} q_{i} -\\beta _{1} \\alpha _{0} -\\beta _{1} u_{i} =\\alpha _{1} q_{i} -\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{2} x_{i} -\\alpha _{1} \\zeta _{i}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\alpha _{1} q_{i} -\\beta _{1} q_{i} =-\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1} -\\beta _{1} u_{i} +\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} +\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\alpha _{1} \\zeta _{i}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "q_{i}( \\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}) =\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1} +\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\alpha _{1} \\zeta _{i} -\\beta _{1} u_{i} \\longrightarrow q_{i} =\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1} +\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{2} x_{i} +\\alpha _{1} \\zeta _{i} -\\beta _{1} u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\therefore q_{i} =\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{0} -\\alpha _{0} \\beta _{1}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} +\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\beta _{2}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}} x_{i} +\\frac{\\alpha _{1} \\zeta _{i} -\\beta _{1} u_{i}}{\\alpha _{1} -\\beta _{1}}\n",
        "\\end{array}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SPaY-GMtb1ev"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "En este punto, si fue posible instrumentar correctamente la variable endogena, muestre que debería pasar que $Cov(x_i, \\zeta_i) = 0$. Es decir, es esperado que no exista información endógena. Así,  aseguraríamos que $Cov(x_i, u_i) = 0$."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "g65o76-6Okiw"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Solución Ejercicio 1.2.4:"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "I11SQZG3O56s"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "I) Añadiendo a los recordatorios anteriores:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\mathbb{E}[ \\zeta _{i}] =0$\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\mathbb{E}[ x_{i} \\cdot \\zeta _{i}] =\\mathbb{E}[ x_{i}] \\cdot \\mathbb{E}[ \\zeta _{i}] \\longrightarrow$ Pues $\\zeta_i$ no está correlacionado con $x_i$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Mb7QonIgO-jI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "II) Calculando la $Cov(x_i, \\zeta_i)$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\begin{array}{{>{\\displaystyle}l}}\n",
        "Cov( x_{i} ,\\zeta _{i}) =\\mathbb{E}( x_{i} \\cdot \\zeta _{i}) -\\mathbb{E}[ x_{i}] \\cdot \\mathbb{E}[ \\zeta _{i}] =\\mathbb{E}[ x_{i}] \\cdot \\mathbb{E}[ \\zeta _{i}] -\\mathbb{E}[ x_{i}] \\cdot \\mathbb{E}[ \\zeta _{i}] =0\\\\\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "\\therefore Cov( x_{i} ,\\zeta _{i}) =0\n",
        "\\end{array}$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eoRPARuoeWPq"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Esto debido a que si $x_i$ es exógena, no habría información de $x_i$ contenida en el termino de error de $\\zeta_i$."
      ],
